info.headline: Flood Advisory issued October 10 at 12:33PM EDT until October 10 at 1:30PM EDT by NWS Key West FL
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...Portions of the Lower Keys.
* WHEN...Until 130 PM EDT.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Water over roadways. Overflowing poor drainage areas.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1233 PM EDT, National Weather Service Meteorologist detected heavy rain due to thunderstorms, exacerbating existing saltwater flooding from seasonal King Tides. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the advisory area. Between 1 and 3 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 3 inches are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Key West, Boca Chica Channel Bridge, Boca Chica, Big Coppitt Key, Key Haven, Fleming Key, Sunset Key, Geiger Key and Shark Key. - This includes US 1 between mile markers 0 and 11. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction:
Do not drive your vehicle into areas where the water covers the roadway. The water depth may be too great to allow your car to cross safely.
Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

parameter.value: FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 130 PM EDT THIS AFTERNOON
